Command Name	Function Description	Opcode (Bits)	Parameters

LOAD_DATA	Load data from host or memory to the Unified Buffer	00000001	Source Address (16 bits), Buffer ID (8 bits)
STORE_DATA	Store data from Unified Buffer or Accumulator to memory	00000010	Destination Address (16 bits), Buffer ID (8 bits)
LOAD_WEIGHTS	Load weights into Weight FIFO	00000011	Source Address (16 bits), FIFO ID (8 bits)
STREAM_TO_FIFO	Stream data sequentially into the FIFO buffer	00000100	Data Address (16 bits), FIFO ID (8 bits)
CLEAR_BUFFER	Clear data in the specified buffer	00000101	Buffer ID (8 bits)
MATRIX_MUL_START	Start matrix multiplication in MMU	00001000	Buffer ID (8 bits), Matrix Dimensions (8 bits each for rows/cols)
MATRIX_ADD	Add two matrices	00001001	Buffer IDs for Source and Destination (8 bits each)
DOT_PRODUCT	Compute the dot product of two vectors	00001010	Buffer IDs for Source and Destination (8 bits each)
ELEMENTWISE_MUL	Perform element-wise multiplication between matrices	00001011	Buffer IDs for Source and Destination (8 bits each)
SETUP_SYSTOLIC_ARRAY	Initialize systolic array parameters	00001100	Array Size (8 bits each for rows and columns)
SYSTOLIC_ARRAY_STEP	Advance the systolic array processing one step	00001101	Step Count (8 bits)
CONFIGURE_SYSTOLIC_PARAMS	Set systolic array parameters	00001110	Direction (4 bits), Row/Column Counts (4 bits each)
LOAD_FIFO	Load data into FIFO buffer for processing	00010000	Source Address (16 bits), FIFO ID (8 bits)
READ_FIFO	Read data out of FIFO and process	00010001	FIFO ID (8 bits), Destination Buffer ID (8 bits)
FIFO_FLUSH	Clear FIFO to prepare for new data	00010010	FIFO ID (8 bits)
SET_PARAMETERS	Set operational parameters like precision	00010100	Parameter ID (8 bits), Value (8 bits)
NOP	No operation, used for synchronization	00010101	None
SYNC	Synchronize components before next operation	00010110	None
WAIT	Wait for a specific condition (e.g., data ready)	00010111	Condition Code (8 bits)
APPLY_ACTIVATION	Apply specified activation function	00011000	Activation Type (4 bits), Buffer ID (8 bits)
NORMALIZE	Normalize data in the buffer	00011001	Buffer ID (8 bits), Scaling Factor (8 bits)
POOL	Apply pooling operation (e.g., Max, Avg)	00011010	Pooling Type (4 bits), Region Size (8 bits)
CLIP	Clip data to a specified range	00011011	Min/Max Values (8 bits each)
ACCUMULATE	Accumulate values in accumulator	00011100	Source Buffer ID (8 bits)
CLEAR_ACCUMULATOR	Reset the accumulator to zero	00011101	Accumulator ID (8 bits)
STORE_ACCUMULATOR	Store accumulated results to memory	00011110	Destination Address (16 bits)
SOFTMAX	Compute softmax function on data in buffer	00100000	Buffer ID (8 bits)
LSTM_GATE	Compute gate for LSTM cell	00100001	Buffer IDs for Inputs and Outputs (8 bits each)
CONV2D	Perform 2D convolution	00100010	Buffer IDs for Input, Weights, and Output (8 bits each)
BATCH_NORM	Apply batch normalization	00100011	Buffer ID (8 bits), Mean/Variance IDs (8 bits each)